cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the redesign of modern distributed DBMSs to take advantage of high-performance RDMA-capable networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) due to the focus on network performance and architecture. Additionally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) may also be relevant due to the proposed redesigns for OLTP, OLAP, and analytical frameworks.
